\frac{4}{2N+3}&\le 4\times 10^{-5}

2N+3 &\ge 10^5

N&\ge \frac{10^5-3}{2}=5\times 10^4-\frac{3}{2}=50,000-1.5


Since n must be an integer, we need to add up the terms from n=0 to n=49,999. That is, we add up the first 50,000 terms.

